cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a model of large-scale predator-prey ecosystems using multi-agent deep reinforcement learning. This work involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The use of multi-agent simulations also suggests that it could belong to the cs.MA sub-category. The incorporation of a real-time evolutionary algorithm and the study of the agents' physical properties suggest that it could also belong to the cs.SY and cs.NE sub-categories.
